lyrics:
Do You Know the Way to San Jose Lyrics[Intro]
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)

[Verse 1]
Do you know the way to San Jose?
I've been away so long
I may go wrong and lose my way
Do you know the way to San Jose?
I'm going back to find
Some peace of mind in San Jose

[Bridge]
L.A. is a great big freeway
Put a hundred down and buy a car
In a week, maybe two
They'll make you a star
Weeks turn into years, how quick they pass
And all the stars that never were
Are parking cars and pumping gas
[Verse 2]
You can really breathe in San Jose
They've got a lot of space
There'll be a place where I can stay
I was born and raised in San Jose
I'm going back to find
Some peace of mind in San Jose

[Bridge]
Fame and fortune is a magnet
It can pull you far away from home
With a dream in your heart you're never alone
Dreams turn into dust and blow away
And there you are, without a friend
You pack your car and ride away

[Chorus]
I've got lots of friends in San Jose
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)
Do you know the way to San Jose?
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)

[Instrumental Break]

[Bridge]
Oh, L.A. is a great big freeway
Put a hundred down and buy a car
In a week, maybe two
They'll make you a star
Weeks turn into years, how quick they pass
And all the stars that never were
Are parking cars and pumping gas
[Outro]
I've got lots of friends in San Jose
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)
Oh, oh, do you know the way to San Jose?
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)
Hmm, can't wait to get back to San Jose
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)
(Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa)
